### 4. wait() — Waiting for Notification

```java
synchronized(obj) {
    obj.wait();    // ← BLOCKS until notify() called
}
```

```
What happens:
─────────────
Thread calls wait()
Thread releases the lock
Thread state → WAITING (indefinitely)
CPU leaves this thread

Another thread must call:
obj.notify()    → wakes ONE waiting thread
obj.notifyAll() → wakes ALL waiting threads
```

```
Real example:
─────────────
Producer thread → produces data → notify()
Consumer thread → waits for data → wait()

Consumer BLOCKS until Producer notifies!
```

---

### 5. join() — Waiting for Another Thread

```java
Thread t1 = new Thread(() -> downloadSong());
t1.start();
t1.join();   // ← main thread BLOCKS here
             //   waits for t1 to finish
System.out.println("download complete!");
```

```
What happens:
─────────────
main thread calls t1.join()
main thread state → WAITING
CPU leaves main thread
t1 thread runs and finishes
main thread wakes up → RUNNABLE
```

```
Timeline:
main    ████ ░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░ ████
             waiting for t1
t1      ░░░░ ████████████░░░ ░░░░
             running
```

