### 6. Heavy Computation — CPU Busy Block

```java
// This does NOT block the thread
// But keeps CPU busy on this thread only!
for (int i = 0; i < 1_000_000_000; i++) {
    result += i * i;  // heavy math
}
```

```
What happens:
─────────────
Thread is RUNNABLE (not blocked!)
But CPU is fully busy on this calculation
Other threads get less CPU time
This is NOT blocking — it's CPU bound work

Thread state → RUNNING (not WAITING)
```

---

### 7. Object Creation — Minor Pause

```java
// Creating many objects
for (int i = 0; i < 1_000_000; i++) {
    new Song("title", "artist");  // heap allocation
}
```

```
What happens:
─────────────
JVM heap fills up
GC (Garbage Collector) kicks in
GC pauses ALL threads momentarily!
This is called → "Stop The World" pause
All threads → BLOCKED briefly
GC cleans heap
All threads → RUNNABLE again
```

