## 🎵 Back to MusicPlayer Example

```java
public void playSong() {
    Thread.sleep(5000);       // ← type 1: time block
}

public void downloadSong() {
    url.openStream();         // ← type 2: I/O block
    fileWriter.write(data);   // ← type 2: I/O block
}

public void likeSong() {
    statement.executeQuery(); // ← type 2: DB/network block
}
```

```
All 3 methods are I/O bound — they WAIT for external things
This is EXACTLY why multithreading helps here!

While downloadSong() waits for network data →
  playSong() can keep playing! ✅
  likeSong() can send request! ✅

CPU is free to switch between threads!
```

---

## 🧠 Key Insight

```
Two types of tasks:

I/O Bound (use Multithreading!) ✅
────────────────────────────────
→ Reading files
→ Network calls
→ Database queries
→ Thread.sleep()
Thread waits most of the time
CPU can run other threads = big win!

CPU Bound (multithreading helps less)
──────────────────────────────────────
→ Heavy calculations
→ Image/video processing
→ Sorting huge data
CPU is busy the whole time
Need more CORES not more threads
```

