## Thread State Flow

```
NEW
 ↓
RUNNABLE ←─────────────────────────┐
 ↓                                 │
RUNNING                            │
 ↓                                 │
 ├─→ sleep()     → TIMED_WAITING ──┤
 ├─→ wait()      → WAITING ────────┤
 ├─→ join()      → WAITING ────────┤
 ├─→ I/O call    → BLOCKED ────────┤
 └─→ sync lock   → BLOCKED ────────┘
 ↓
TERMINATED
```

---

*Remember: CPU never truly blocks — threads do! CPU always finds other work to do! 🚀*
